############################################################
### How to fix the SVG files that comes out from Omix... ###
############################################################

1) compact the SVG format (eg make the g elements pretty, remove duplicated rows)
   will create a new file ER.svg.fixed.svg.unique.svg in the src/assets/maps/compartment_level folder
   (one compartment at the time...)
perl fixOutput.pl ER
perl fixOutput.pl nucleosome

2) then figure out the coordinate match for one of the pathways in the ER
   (all compartments at once)
   by manually looking at the output the adjust values were determined...

3) then change the coordinate system in the SVG file to match and add the corresponding id
python update.py --addID

4) when you want to change the colors, try
python update.py --changeColorFor test
